_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟠 Major_ | _⚡ Quick win_

**Debounce geometry persistence to avoid drag-time localStorage churn.**

`persistDockGeometry` currently runs on every geometry update, including pointer-move drag frames. Synchronous storage writes on this hot path can introduce UI jank.



<details>
<summary>Proposed fix</summary>

```diff
+ const persistTimeoutRef = React.useRef<number | null>(null);

  React.useEffect(() => {
-   persistDockGeometry(clampDockGeometry(geometry));
+   if (persistTimeoutRef.current) {
+     window.clearTimeout(persistTimeoutRef.current);
+   }
+   persistTimeoutRef.current = window.setTimeout(() => {
+     persistDockGeometry(clampDockGeometry(geometry));
+     persistTimeoutRef.current = null;
+   }, 150);
+   return () => {
+     if (persistTimeoutRef.current) {
+       window.clearTimeout(persistTimeoutRef.current);
+       persistTimeoutRef.current = null;
+     }
+   };
  }, [geometry]);
```
